1. Selenium Relative locations | Friendly locators

above() : Element located above with respect to the specified element 
below() : Element located below with respect to the specified element
toLeftOf()  : Element located to left with respect to the specified element
toRightOf() : Element located to right with respect to the specified element

2. Syntax: 
   driver.findElement(with TagName("xx").above(WebElement);	

3. Relative locators do not support flex element

4. Invoking multiple windows/tabs available form Selenium 4.0 version